commit.message:
Makefile.in: stamp-lib* -> s-lib*.

        * Makefile.in: stamp-lib* -> s-lib*.
        * libU77/Makefile.in: Likewise.
        * libF77/Makefile.in: Likewise.
        * libI77/Makefile.in: Likewise.

From-SVN: r21162

files.patch:
@@ -4,6 +4,11 @@ Tue Jul 14 21:35:30 1998  Gerald Pfeifer  <pfeifer@dbai.tuwien.ac.at>
 
 Tue Jul 14 02:16:34 1998  Jeffrey A Law  (law@cygnus.com)
 
+	* Makefile.in: stamp-lib* -> s-lib*.
+	* libU77/Makefile.in: Likewise.
+	* libF77/Makefile.in: Likewise.
+	* libI77/Makefile.in: Likewise.
+
 	* libU77/Makefile.in (ALL_CFLAGS): Add -I$(F2C_H_DIR).
 
 1998-07-06  Mike Stump  <mrs@wrs.com>

@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@ all: i77 f77 u77 e77
 
 i77 f77 u77: g2c.h
 
-$(LIBG2C): stamp-libi77 stamp-libf77 stamp-libu77 stamp-libe77
+$(LIBG2C): s-libi77 s-libf77 s-libu77 s-libe77
 	rm -f $(LIBG2C)
 	set -e; \
 	for i in $(SUBDIRS); \
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@ f77:
 u77:
 	cd libU77; $(MAKE) $(FLAGS_TO_PASS) all
 
-stamp-libe77: $(srcdir)/f2cext.c
+s-libe77: $(srcdir)/f2cext.c
 	if [ -d libE77 ]; then rm -f libE77/*.o; else mkdir libE77; fi
 	for name in $(F2CEXT); \
 	do \
@@ -111,7 +111,7 @@ stamp-libe77: $(srcdir)/f2cext.c
 	    -o libE77/L$${name}.o; \
 	  if [ $$? -eq 0 ] ; then true; else exit 1; fi; \
 	done
-	echo timestamp >stamp-libe77
+	echo timestamp >s-libe77
 
 ${srcdir}/configure: ${srcdir}/configure.in
 	rm -f config.cache
@@ -173,7 +173,7 @@ clean: mostlyclean
 	for i in $(SUBDIRS); do (cd $$i && $(MAKE) clean); done
 
 distclean: clean
-	rm -f Makefile config.cache config.status g2c.h stamp-libe77
+	rm -f Makefile config.cache config.status g2c.h s-libe77
 	for i in $(SUBDIRS); do (cd $$i && $(MAKE) distclean); done
 
 maintainer-clean:

@@ -80,10 +80,10 @@ F90BIT = lbitbits.o lbitshft.o qbitbits.o qbitshft.o
 OBJS = $(MISC) $(POW) $(CX) $(DCX) $(REAL) $(DBL) $(INT) \
 	 $(HALF) $(CMP) $(EFL) $(CHAR) $(F90BIT)
 
-all: ../stamp-libf77
+all: ../s-libf77
 
-../stamp-libf77: $(OBJS)
-	echo timestamp > ../stamp-libf77
+../s-libf77: $(OBJS)
+	echo timestamp > ../s-libf77
 
 archive:
 	$(AR) $(ARFLAGS) $(LIBG2C) $(OBJS)
@@ -116,7 +116,7 @@ clean: mostlyclean
 	rm -f config.log
 
 distclean: clean
-	rm -f config.cache config.status Makefile ../stamp-libf77 configure
+	rm -f config.cache config.status Makefile ../s-libf77 configure
 
 maintainer-clean:

@@ -61,10 +61,10 @@ OBJ =	VersionI.o backspace.o close.o dfe.o dolio.o due.o endfile.o err.o \
 	util.o wref.o wrtfmt.o wsfe.o wsle.o wsne.o xwsne.o \
 	ftell_.o
 
-all: ../stamp-libi77
+all: ../s-libi77
 
-../stamp-libi77: $(OBJ)
-	echo timestamp > ../stamp-libi77
+../s-libi77: $(OBJ)
+	echo timestamp > ../s-libi77
 
 archive:
 	$(AR) $(ARFLAGS) $(LIBG2C) $(OBJ)
@@ -149,7 +149,7 @@ clean: mostlyclean
 	rm -f config.log
 
 distclean: clean
-	rm -f config.cache config.status Makefile ../stamp-libi77 configure
+	rm -f config.cache config.status Makefile ../s-libi77 configure
 
 maintainer-clean:

@@ -80,10 +80,10 @@ SRCS =  Version.c gerror_.c perror_.c ierrno_.c itime_.c time_.c \
 	umask_.c sys_clock_.c date_.c second_.c flush1_.c mclock_.c \
 	alarm_.c datetime_.c
 
-all: ../stamp-libu77
+all: ../s-libu77
 
-../stamp-libu77: $(OBJS)
-	echo timestamp > ../stamp-libu77
+../s-libu77: $(OBJS)
+	echo timestamp > ../s-libu77
 
 archive:
 	$(AR) $(ARFLAGS) $(LIBG2C) $(OBJS)
@@ -184,7 +184,7 @@ clean: mostlyclean
 
 distclean: clean
 	rm -f config.cache config.status Makefile config.h stamp.h \
-	  ../stamp-libu77 configure
+	  ../s-libu77 configure
 
 maintainer-clean:
